    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Upright serpents developed by the Parisian maker Forveille around 1833, made of brass with a wood bell, and having two sharp U-shaped bends, six fingerholes, three or four keys, and a crook to carry the mouthpiece.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Serpentones verticales desarrollados por el fabricante parisino Forveille alrededor de 1833, construídos en bronce con una campana de madera, y que tienen dos curvas agudas en forma de U, seis orificios para los dedos, tres o cuatro llaves, y un codo que lleva la boquilla.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Serpenten, koper met houten klankbeker, 2 scherpe U-vormige krommingen, 6 vingergaten, 3 of 4 kleppen, kromme aanblaasbuis met mondstuk, rechtopstaand; Parijs, rond 1833.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052452/Encyclopedie van muziekinstrumenten (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>直立式的蛇形號，約於西元1833年，由巴黎的樂器師傅佛維耶所發明，以黃銅製成，有一個木製號口、兩道尖銳的U字形彎道、6個指孔、3或4個鍵，以及一個裝有吹嘴的變音管。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gerader Serpent, entwickelt von dem Pariser Instrumentenbauer Forveille um 1833, hergestellt aus Messing mit einem Schalltrichter aus Holz und mit zwei scharfen U-förmigen Biegungen, sechs Fingerlöchern, drei oder vier Klappen und einem Aufsatzbogen für das Kesselmundstück.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
